{
  "stem": "22869.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "With my parents at home, we spoke like half Yiddish and half German.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I know, when I was in the yeshiva, in the higher school of learning, our correspondence with my parents were in German.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was in Jewish letters.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The alphabet was Jewish, but the pronunciation was German.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, technically, I would say, living in the Czechoslovakian Republic, that we probably belonged to the German minority-- sounds very laughing, I mean, even to state this-- but we belonged to the German minority in-- in-- in the Slovakia city of Michalovce.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I even went-- I even took German in school.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1942, the first thing that happened in the middle of March, approximately, when they were starting to gather and take away girls, a lot of people sent their young daughters-- talking about 18, 19, 20, 21, 22-- to Hungary, of course illegally.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because in Hungary, the Jewish people were not touched yet, officially.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So in order to escape being taken away by the Slovaks and then delivered to the Germans, my father decided that he's going to send my-- my oldest sister, who is today in Israel, to Hungary.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we found some connection.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And for money, of course-- we were supposed to, my two brothers were supposed to go with her, which they in fact did, to a neighboring city of Trebisov.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there they paid a guy who was supposed to smuggle her across the border.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Except that this guy took the money, and he turned around and notified the police.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And both my two brothers and my sister were captured by the police, and put on a train and brought back to our hometown.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
